The Academic Instructor is required to teach the courses in the undergraduate programs offered by the University at Buffalo, The State University of New York, US, in partnership with Singapore Institute of Management in Singapore.
The roles would include:
• Course design and implementation of course syllabi to meet UB learning objectives;
• Create and administer assessment instruments;
• Evaluate student progress and achievements;
• Hold regular consultation hours;
• Maintain and submit academic records.

Job Requirements:
• A Ph.D or Master's Degree in related discipline from a reputable university.
• At least 2 years of relevant teaching experience at the tertiary level is preferred
• 5 years of relevant work experience will be an added advantage
• Familiarity with Blackboard is a plus